akas: Man v. Food Nation USA (fourth season title)
akas from release info: Man v. Food Nation USA (fourth season title)

1.title: Minneapolis, MN
1.plot: Casey stops in Minneapolis -- home of the Juicy Lucy, a burger with a secret. Other stops include the Blue Door Pub and Betty Danger's Country Club. At Lu's Sandwich, Webb faces off against a 3 foot long Bahn Mi sandwich.

2.title: Saint Paul, MN
2.plot: Casey Webb's latest delicious detour brings him to Saint Paul for an indoor food truck park, a timeless diner and a terrible twosome of crepes and Thai rolled ice cream.

3.title: Worcester, MA
3.plot: Casey visits Worcester, MA. The featured items sampled include: The Roasted Tomato and Black Garlic Ramen with Grilled Cheese at Broth, The Peanut Butter Cup Stuffed French Toast at the Miss Worcester Diner and The Maddness Challenge at The Boynton Restaurant.

4.title: Baltimore, MD
4.plot: Casey Webb's epic eating expedition brings him to Baltimore for an out-of-this-world diner, a classic crab feast and a four-pound pho fight.

5.title: Savannah, GA
5.plot: Casey Webb travels down to Georgia to taste some the Savannah's best fried chicken, low country seafood boil and a four-pound pulled pork sandwich known only as the Pigzilla.

6.title: Atlanta, GA
6.plot: Casey Webb's cross-country culinary crusade brings him to Atlanta for a decadent doughnut brunch, beastly barbecue and a five-pound mountain of tater tot nachos.

7.title: Orange County, CA
7.plot: Casey Webb cruises into Orange County, California, to take on a three-pound burger slathered in a sauce made from three of the spiciest peppers on the planet.

8.title: Palm Springs, CA
8.plot: Casey's cross-country culinary quest takes him back in time to Palm Springs, California, where he comes face-to-face with a three-pound skyscraper of a sandwich loaded with every deli meat imaginable.

9.title: Duluth, MN
9.plot: Casey Webb heads to Duluth, Minnesota, where he tastes the city's best fish fry, visits a specialty sandwich shop and attempts to finish a three-pound platter of pie and ice cream in 20 minutes.

10.title: Jersey Shore, NJ
10.plot: Casey visits his hometown, including the Speak Eatery, home of the Hand Grenade--a sandwich with ribs and mac 'n cheese. Other stops include Bahr's Landing for a 6 lb. crabmeat-stuffed lobster and Papa Pancho for the Spicy Pizza Challenge.

11.title: Phoenix, AZ
11.plot: Casey Webb heads to Arizona to unearth the Phoenix's most appetizing eats and take on eight wings slather in a scorching ghost chili and habanero sauce plus two whole grilled habanero peppers.

12.title: Maui, HI
12.plot: Casey travels to the Cool Cat Cafe in Maui to take on the 808 Burger Challenge. Some of the other things he tries in Maui are the Polynesian Paralysis Loco Moco at Da Kitchen and the Banana Macadamia Nut Pancake at Grandma's Coffee House.

13.title: Cincinnati, OH
13.plot: Casey is in Cincinnati Ohio at Roc-a-Fellas Pizza for the Bronx Bomber Challenge. Along the way he samples the Yo Mama burger at Arnold's Bar and Grill and the No Freakin' Way chili platter at Blue Ash Chili.

14.title: Indianapolis, IN
14.plot: Casey travels to Indianapolis Indiana for the Monstar Challenge at Mug-n-Bun. While here, he samples the local offerings. These include: Super Spicy Cocktail Shrimp and a 38oz Bone-In Prime Rib at St. Elmo Steak House and the Breakfast Mac and Cheese at The Loft Restaurant at Traderspoint Creamery.

1.title: Amarillo
1.plot: Host Adam Richman takes on a spicy "burger from Hell" in Amarillo, TX.

2.title: Memphis
2.plot: Adam heads to Memphis, Tennessee, to get some deep-fried Southern cooking.

3.title: Pittsburgh
3.plot: Adam grabs a mouthwatering sandwich from the famed Primanti Brothers.

4.title: Columbus
4.plot: Adam Richman travels to Columbus, Ohio, to tailgate with Buckeye fans.

5.title: Austin
5.plot: Adam travels to Austin, Texas, for a breakfast taco challenge.

6.title: Chicago
6.plot: Adam visits the Windy City to chow down on Chi-town-style deep-dish pizza.

7.title: Atlanta
7.plot: In Atlanta, Adam tackles the 11-pound Carnivore Pizza Challenge.

8.title: Boston

10.title: New Orleans
10.plot: Host Adam Richman is chowing down massive po' boys at Mother's Restaurant.

14.plot: Adam Richman visits St. Louis to chow down on Monte Cristo hot dogs.

15.title: San Jose

16.plot: Adam visits the Mile-High City for some Rocky Mountain oysters.

18.title: Minneapolis

15.plot: Adam returns home to Brooklyn for the Suicide 6 Wings Challenge.

16.plot: Adam visits Alaska for a monstrous challenge: the six-pound Kodiak Arrest.

17.plot: Adam accepts the Shut Up Juice spicy pulled-pork challenge in Little Rock.

18.plot: Adam Richman visits Tucson for a hot dog wrapped in bacon and fixins.

20.plot: Adam Richman is off to Hartford, Connecticut, for some humongous hot dogs.

21.plot: Adam was the first to finish Don Shula's steak challenge in 20 minutes.

15.plot: Adam has a date with a steak at the Riverstone Grill in Niagara Falls.

16.title: Butte
16.plot: Adam Richman visits Big Sky Country in historic Butte, Montana.

17.title: Sacramento
17.plot: Adam is in sunny Sacramento, California, for a taste of the Golden State.

18.title: Des Moines
18.plot: Adam Richman is in Des Moines, Iowa, for some Midwestern comfort food.

20.title: Ann Arbor
20.plot: Adam Richman heads to Ann Arbor, Michigan, home of the Michigan Wolverines.

1.title: New Haven
1.plot: Adam persuades Ric to devour 10 grilled cheese sandwiches in one hour.

2.plot: Adam coaches wrestler Jerry Sags in the Davy Jones hot wing challenge.

3.plot: Adam guides country music stars through 72 ounces of steak in Nashville.

6.title: Mobile
6.plot: "Big" Joe Evans hopes to regain his crown at the Oyster House.

7.plot: Adam coaches in a conch-eating contest and singer Vanilla Ice shows up.

8.title: Gulf Coast

10.title: Louisville

11.title: Milwaukee
11.plot: In Milwaukee, Adam helps a local stay undefeated against food challengers.

13.title: Dallas
13.plot: Adam helps a Texan take down five pounds of Vietnamese pho in Dallas.

14.title: Route 66
14.plot: Adam leads a Navy officer in the Puffy Taco Challenge.

15.title: Harlem
15.plot: Adam Richman is in Harlem, New York for some soul food and to guide the Harlem Globetrotters through the Squealer challenge at Rack & Soul.

16.title: Pacific Coast Highway
16.plot: Adam journeys the PCH to guide a teacher in the Brahma Bull Challenge.

17.title: Street Eats
17.plot: Adam journeys to Tampa, NYC and L.A. to hit the nation's best street carts.

18.plot: Adam coaches a local to win the Juicy Lucy Challenge in St. Paul, MN.

19.title: Cincinnati

20.plot: Adam roots for NASCAR's Joey Logano on the track and in a food challenge.

1.title: New York City
1.plot: The show's new host, Casey Webb, takes on the NY City's Pick Your Poison Challenge (150 ounce milkshake, 8 pound Sloppy Joes or 6 habanero ghost chilly wings). He also tries the fondue burger and pizza topped with pizza inside a pizza.

2.title: Milwaukee
2.plot: Casey travels to Milwaukee for some epic Brew City eats, including a pitcher-sized Bloody Mary garnished with a whole chicken and a four-and-a-half-pound Reuben sandwich challenge.

3.title: Charleston, SC
3.plot: Casey heads to Charleston, SC, for epic low country eats. He takes on the Belt Buster Challenge in which he must consume a two-pound burger, three pounds of nachos, an order of tater tots and a 12-ounce milkshake in 20 minutes.

4.title: New Orleans, LA
4.plot: Casey heads to New Orleans to taste the best of the Big Easy, including a mammoth po' boy and a four-pound sundae packed with eight large scoops of ice cream and smothered with eight different toppings.

5.title: Sleepy Hollow, NY
5.plot: Casey visits Sleepy Hollow, NY, where he tries the massive Headless Horseman Burger and takes on the Dawg House Challenge in which a roll of the dice chooses 12 insanely topped hot dogs that he must eat in under 30 minutes.

6.title: Houston, TX
6.plot: Casey two-steps down to Houston, TX, for some Tex-Mex tastiness, including a colossal 22-ounce chicken-fried steak and the ultimate spicy challenge -- a burger topped with seven of the world's hottest chile peppers.

7.title: Portland, OR
7.plot: Casey heads to Portland, OR, to taste mouthwatering Peruvian chicken, a succulent porchetta sandwich and a two-pound burrito packed with ten of the spiciest peppers in the world.

8.title: Chicago, IL
8.plot: Casey travels to Chicago for some epic Windy City eats, including a massive triple-threat pork sandwich and a challenge featuring a two-pound double bacon cheeseburger and two pounds of "Irish Nacho" cheese fries.

9.title: Des Moines, IA
9.plot: Casey heads to Des Moines, IA, where he'll attempt the eat an overstuffed pulled pork sandwich slathered in a scorpion pepper hot sauce in ten minutes.

10.title: Bllings, MT
10.plot: Casey travels to Billings, MT, to tackle a one-hour steak challenge featuring a 78-ounce rib eye and two pounds of mashed potatoes, salad and bread.

1.title: Boston, MA
1.plot: Casey travels to historic Boston, MA, for some epic New England eats and a 4.5-pound Irish breakfast challenge at Flann O'Brien's Pub.

2.title: Burlington, VT
2.plot: Casey travels to the small town of Burlington, VT, for some mammoth eats, including a beer-infused bagel feast and a 3.5-pound breakfast sandwich challenge.

3.title: Louisville, KY
3.plot: Casey travels to Louisville, KY, for some epic eats, including a booze-infused Southern staple and a one-of-a-kind spicy popcorn and frozen hot chocolate challenge in nearby Santa Claus, IN.

4.title: St. Louis, MO
4.plot: Casey Webb visits St. Louis, Missouri, in search of the biggest and best the city has to offer. He encounters a four-pound meatball and tackles a New York-style pizza so massive he'll need the help of a partner to take it down.

5.title: Philadelphia, PA
5.plot: Casey sails to Philadelphia to tackle the epic Classic Whale Challenge, a 13-pound bagel sandwich stuffed with cream cheese, nova salmon, whitefish, tomatoes and onions.

6.title: Seattle, WA
6.plot: Casey attacks Seattle. The challenge is a super hot chicken wing challenge.

7.title: Los Angeles, CA
7.plot: Casey Webb travels to sunny Los Angeles for some epic eats, including a 2.5-pound fusion burrito loaded with every ingredient in the kitchen and drenched in hot sauce 600 times hotter than a jalapeno.

8.title: San Diego, CA
8.plot: Casey travels to San Diego to face off against a 5.5-pound stack of pancakes layered with bacon, eggs, sausage, country-fried steak and thick-cut ham.

9.title: Pittsburgh, PA
9.plot: Casey heads to Pittsburgh for creative eats and a five-pound sandwich loaded with meat, cheese, fries and coleslaw.

10.title: Daytona Beach, FL
10.plot: Casey's delicious mission brings him to Daytona Beach, FL, where he takes on a mammoth three-tier sandwich stacked with two burgers, six pieces of mahi mahi, two pieces of Texas toast and a ten-ounce bun.

12.title: Grand Rapids, MI
12.plot: Casey travels to Grand Rapids, Michigan, where he takes on a five-pound tray loaded with chili dogs, French fries, beer-battered onion rings and a 20-ounce soda.

13.title: Ozark Mountains
13.plot: Casey travels over the Ozarks to tackle the Goliath, a massive cupcake equal to 22 regular-sized cupcakes.

14.title: Nashville, TN
14.plot: Casey's mouthwatering mission brings him to Tennessee, where he faces his hottest challenge yet -- three jumbo chicken tenders smothered in a Carolina Reaper-infused sauce.

imdb.title: Man v. Food
plot: Host Adam Richman (and subsequently Casey Webb) travels around the U.S., taking on a variety of local eating challenges involving meal size, spiciness and other daunting factors.::scgary66 (updated by Anonymous)
